column167: The question about student achievement being related to poverty or race it’s kind of a trick question. Race is absolutely nothing to do with it. And neither does poverty. You can dump all The money you want into a school but that’s not going to change the mindset of the impoverished people. That’s not gonna get parents to tell kids that it’s good to go to school or to help them with their schoolwork and home and engage. Giving a bunch of money to school districts is not gonna make household in the community raise children responsibility and discipline and to try take care.  It’s a mindset of impoverished people that is passed down that keeps them impoverished.  In my short time teaching students and parents are given more than enough for the kids to be educated and that is in a poor school.  Been doing well in school is more about the nurture received in the household than it is about the Nature of the situation.
